<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
    <head>
        <% include ../partials/header.ejs %>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="login">
            <h1>Please Login</h1>
            <form action="/login/authentication" method="get">
                <label class="indent" for="username">Username</label>
                <input class="indent" id="username" type="text" name="username">
                <label class="indent" for="password">Password</label>
                <input class="indent" id="password" type="password" name="password">
                <button type="submit">Submit</button>
            </form>
            <p>This is a sample Node application deployed to Heroku. It's a reasonably simple app - but a good foundation for understanding how to get the most out of the Heroku platform.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
